      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey so im having a weird issue with my sourdough starter. i keep it at a super consistent 78 degrees but the rise is really inconsistent. like some days it's bubbly and great, and other days it's just... flat and dead looking. can you explain what's actually happening with the yeast and bacteria during fermentation? like why would the activity fluctuate so much if the temp is stable?",
