    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "<|channel>thought\n<channel|>That makes sense. So it's basically a competition between different organisms for the same nutrients? It's just weird because it feels like there's something unseen or invisible happening that I can't control. If the temperature is spot on, what else could be causing those huge swings in activity levels besides just the feeding ratio?",
