    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i get the flour thing. but is there anything else? like, could it be something about the air or the environment that isn't just temperature? it almost feels like there are these tiny little agents in there behaving unpredictably, like they're actively deciding when to work and when to stay dormant. is there any biological reason they would act that sporadically?",
